INSERT INTO FISH (ID, NAME, FAMILY, LOOK, PHOTO, OCCURRENCE, TIME_TO_FISHING, BAIT, GROUNDBAIT, METHOD_AND_TECHNIQUE, EQUIPMENT, FISHERY, PERIOD_OF_PROTECTION, PROTECTIVE_SIZE, RECORD) VALUES (1, 'GRASS CARP', '', 'It has a slender torso. The back is brown-green, while the sides are golden. Amur are characterized by large scales and low eyes placed close to the mouth. The body is chublike.', 'https://angloo.com/wp-content/uploads/amur-300x143.jpg', 'Origin is China. There, since the tenth century, he was artificially bred and then introduced into many waters. It appeared in Poland for the first time in the 1960s. As it is a thermophilic fish, in Polish conditions it did not settle down enough to start natural spawning. Accordingly, the grasslands come from artificial stocking. In Polish conditions, grass carp is treated as a fishing attraction, or colloquially speaking a live mower, because as a herbivorous fish it is often used to clean overgrown reservoirs.', 'As grass carp is a hot water fish, the fishing season is from early spring to early autumn. The most severe are: June, July, August and also September.', 'We have a large spectrum of possibilities here. On the hook you can put: white and red worms, sundries, bread, corn, boiled potatoes, dough, cherries, Hungarian plums, lettuce leaves, steamed wheat, cane (young shoots), as well as protein balls or fruit or "smelly" pellets.', 'Boiled corn and other grains - peas or lupins - are best groundbait. It should be remembered that this is a species that consumes a significant amount of groundbaits, lures and treats served. It is worth preparing a seat several days earlier, 3-7 days earlier. It can also be baited with protein balls.', 'First of all, carp are caught similarly to carp - using the ground, carp or float method. Quick escapes, usually not in one, but several directions, are his specialty. Therefore, a strong reel and thick line (0.35-0.40mm) are needed. The hook should be adapted to the bait. The rod is from 3.30 m to 3.90 m long. Simply put, the equipment should be adapted to the bravery, and above all the strength of the amur.', 'Float - 0.35 mm fishing line, braided rig, hook from number 4 to number 8, rod, 4 meters, solid reel, float from 5 gram up. Ground - main line 0.33 - 0.35 mm, rod up to 3.90 meters.', 'This fish lives in virtually every water. The best fisheries are: lakes, rivers, ponds, dam reservoirs, oxbow lakes, and sandbanks', 'no protective period', 'no protection dimension', '132 cm and 39.20 kg');
INSERT INTO FISH (ID, NAME, FAMILY, LOOK, PHOTO, OCCURRENCE, TIME_TO_FISHING, BAIT, GROUNDBAIT, METHOD_AND_TECHNIQUE, EQUIPMENT, FISHERY, PERIOD_OF_PROTECTION, PROTECTIVE_SIZE, RECORD) VALUES (2, 'BARBEL (Barbus barbus)', '', 'A slender fish with an elongated body. A characteristic feature is the snout mouth, four whiskers on the upper lip and slightly thicker, you can say meaty lower lip. The barbel ridge turns from brown to olive green. The sides are golden, lighter, while the belly is whitish. Caudal and dorsal fin with a dark, grayish color. The other fins are colored red. Barbel size is usually 30? 50 cm, maximum 100 cm. The physique is typically adapted to bottom life. Barbel roe is poisonous.', 'https://angloo.com/wp-content/uploads/brzana-300x114.jpg', 'Rivers with a fast current, with sandy, stony, gravelly bottom. Barbells like average water temperature, i.e. not too warm, not too cold. During the day they stick to the strong current, all kinds of pits, tributaries. In the evening they flow out into calmer waters.', 'The best time for barbell is summer and autumn. In particular, late summer, i.e. the months August, September, and all October. Given the time of day, mornings and evenings are the best.', 'A classic example of bait is diced yellow cheese. In addition, white worms, earthworms, leeches, peas, cakes, pellets.', 'First of all, pellets, protein balls, loose groundbaits.', 'The best method is a ground method or feeder. It is also worth to include a basket with groundbait in the set. As the barbell is a very strong fish and also swims in swift currents, the hook must be strong, firm.', 'Ground - strong rod, even carp up to 4 meters in length, hook number 4-6, 0.30 mm main line and braided line for rig.', 'Mainly rivers - Vistula, Odra, Warta, wherever the rocky bottom. Rarely in stagnant waters, lakes, dam reservoirs.', 'January 1 - June 30', '40 cm, daily limit - 3 items', '85 cm and 7.00 kg');
INSERT INTO FISH (ID, NAME, FAMILY, LOOK, PHOTO, OCCURRENCE, TIME_TO_FISHING, BAIT, GROUNDBAIT, METHOD_AND_TECHNIQUE, EQUIPMENT, FISHERY, PERIOD_OF_PROTECTION, PROTECTIVE_SIZE, RECORD) VALUES (3, 'ASP (Aspius aspius)', '', 'Asp is characterized by its extended body, which, when viewed from the side, seems a little flattened. It has a pointed head, small eyes and a wide mouth. The lower jaw is slightly longer than the upper one, hooked bent. It can be said that asp has the appearance of an athlete - characterized by well-developed fins and a strong torso, which also affects its predatory appearance. The asp back is steel? silvery fins a red shade, while the sides are slightly lighter. Length from 50 to 75 cm, maximum 120 cm. Maximum weight up to 12 kg. Asp is a predator whose purpose is most often glue and what will fall on the surface of the water, e.g. insects. Due to the fact that asp feeds just below the water surface, it often reveals its location.', 'https://angloo.com/wp-content/uploads/boleń-300x108.jpg', 'Asp can be found in dam reservoirs, lowland rivers or coastal sea waters. The borders of waters of different nature (tributaries, contact of the current and calm water, dams) are a perfect place for asp. As rap mainly feeds on general cargo, we can expect it in places where e.g. herd of bleeds can be found. In cold seasons, it floats rather on a warm bottom, while in summer seasons near the surface.', 'The highest intensities are September and October. Shorter, increased activity falls on the month of April, because it is the time after spawning.', 'First of all, bleak, dead and alive worms, live insects with bright colors, white, red worms, bouquets, wobblers, rippers and other artificial lures.', 'Generally no asp groundbait is used. Loose groundbait may be used to attract small fish that is of interest to asp.', 'The best method for asp is spinning in any form. Swinging plates, spinners, wobblers, twisters of bright colors are used here. In addition, you can fish asp using the ground and float methods.', 'Asp can be fished in many ways. Spinning: It is worth using a rod up to 270 cm long, a line up to 0.22 mm in diameter, and a good quality reel. Ground: Rod up to 390 cm, reel with free running, main line 0.22 mm in diameter. Float: Rod up to 4 meters long, main line 0.20-0.22 mm.', 'Asp can survive in virtually any water. They can be found in rivers (Wisła, Odra, Warta and others), lakes, dam reservoirs and even ponds.', '1 January - 30 April', '40 cm, daily limit - 3 pieces', '89 cm and 8.49 kg');
INSERT INTO FISH (ID, NAME, FAMILY, LOOK, PHOTO, OCCURRENCE, TIME_TO_FISHING, BAIT, GROUNDBAIT, METHOD_AND_TECHNIQUE, EQUIPMENT, FISHERY, PERIOD_OF_PROTECTION, PROTECTIVE_SIZE, RECORD) VALUES (4, 'ZARTE (Vimba vimba)', '', 'Zarte is a medium-sized fish with elongated and laterally flattened body. Typically lower mouth, with crescent-shaped lips. The body is usually silver, and the belly is white, except during the spawning period, when the body is dark - the blue-gray sides seem to be soothed? and orange belly. Even fins. In appearance similar to mumps. The size of the certificate ranges from 20 to 35 cm, and a maximum of 50 cm.', 'https://angloo.com/wp-content/uploads/certa-300x214.jpg', 'Mainly rivers, especially sections with a hard stone bottom. In the colder season they swim deeper, in the warmer season closer to the surface. Certificates can also be found in fresh and coastal marine waters. These are fish that they like to wander. It can be said that they lead a truly nomadic lifestyle (from the Baltic Sea to the Podkarpackie region).', 'The best times are August and September. So we can say that the border between summer and autumn. The weakest bites occur in the autumn months, i.e. October and November.', 'Mainly white worms, pins. You can also put on a hook, red bugs, hard-boiled egg protein, potatoes, pieces of sundew.', 'All kinds of carp fish mixes are great for bait.', 'The best method is a ground method, feeder or float - a flow. Place the bait on the bottom or a little above it. Certy like silence, so you should behave properly on the fishery. The jam must be instant.', 'The best option is to catch these fish from the ground or float. Ground : feeder rod 3.6 - 3.9 meters long with a main line from 0.18 to 0.22 mm, leader with a diameter of 0.12 mm and hook number 12. Float : Rod up to 4-5 meters, a delicate float and a thin line should signal the taking of a complexion.', 'Certificates occur mainly in the rivers - Warta Vistula, Odra and others. In addition, they are found in canals, lakes, reservoirs, dam reservoirs.', '1 January - 30 June', '30 cm, daily limit - 5 pieces.', '51cm and 1.74 kg');
INSERT INTO FISH (ID, NAME, FAMILY, LOOK, PHOTO, OCCURRENCE, TIME_TO_FISHING, BAIT, GROUNDBAIT, METHOD_AND_TECHNIQUE, EQUIPMENT, FISHERY, PERIOD_OF_PROTECTION, PROTECTIVE_SIZE, RECORD) VALUES (5, 'COD (Gadus morhua)', '', 'A characteristic feature of cod is that it has, apart from the caudal, thoracic and abdominal fins, three dorsal and two anal fins. The lower lip of the cod is smaller than the upper one and has a single mustache, which is the sense organ. Cod changes color depending on the habitat. The sides and the back of the cod resemble a marbled pattern in which the colors: gray, olive, beige with red spots predominate.', 'https://angloo.com/wp-content/uploads/dorsz-300x120.jpg', 'Mainly sea water. Cods swim at great depths, several hundred meters from the shore.', 'The best fishing season is May. Autumn months are also a good time, especially in October.', 'Crabs, small sea fish, fish fillets, pilkers imitating Tobias, herring, sprat.', '', 'The basis for cod fishing is a strong rod and reel. Equip yourself with a very strong fishing line or braid, as well as pilkers. Fishing is all about casting the lure to the bottom and jumping it off. The cod''s lips are hard, which is why the treble hook must be sharpened with glance.', '', '','No protection period.', 'No protection dimension, no catch limit.', '');

INSERT INTO FISH (ID, NAME, FAMILY, LOOK, PHOTO, OCCURRENCE, TIME_TO_FISHING, BAIT, GROUNDBAIT, METHOD_AND_TECHNIQUE, EQUIPMENT, FISHERY, PERIOD_OF_PROTECTION, PROTECTIVE_SIZE, RECORD) VALUES (6,
                                                                                                                                                                                                'DANUBE (Hucho hucho)',
                                                                                                                                                                                                '',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'A characteristic feature is the huge head, which is slightly flattened. The head has a wide mouth opening. Ridge of brown or greenish color, red sides, and in older individuals copper, white belly. Unevenly distributed dark spots on the sides. Fished individuals usually do not exceed a meter. The main food is fish: roach, chub, ide.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'https://angloo.com/wp-content/uploads/głowacica-300x235.jpg',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'The danube is a loner. It lives mainly in cold waters with a rocky bottom, with fast-flowing water. Most often it can be found in rivers with a gravel or rocky bottom. It stays in water mainly in deeper places with a strong current.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'The most favorable season is autumn and winter, more precisely the turn of the seasons. Given the time of day, the best time is early in the morning.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Mainly smaller fish, wobblers and plaques.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                ' Do not use groundbait groundbait.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'The best method is spinning. The set must be strong, with a sharp anchor, because the head has bony jaws.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Strong spinning rod and reel. The main line is basically a fishing line, also solid. The whole matched to the size of the fish.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'rivers with a lot of oxygen and rocky or gravelly bottom and fast current',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'March 1 - May 31',
                                                                                                                                                                                                '70 cm, weekly limit - 1 item (from Monday to Sunday)',
                                                                                                                                                                                                ' 120 cm and 20.30 kg');
INSERT INTO FISH (ID, NAME, FAMILY, LOOK, PHOTO, OCCURRENCE, TIME_TO_FISHING, BAIT, GROUNDBAIT, METHOD_AND_TECHNIQUE, EQUIPMENT, FISHERY, PERIOD_OF_PROTECTION, PROTECTIVE_SIZE, RECORD) VALUES (7,
                                                                                                                                                                                                'IDE (Leuciscus idus)',
                                                                                                                                                                                                '',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'The body has a typical carp shape, flattened, ending with a small head with a small muzzle. The color of the back is gray and brown, the sides are silvery, while the belly is white. The fins are reddish, brick red in the lower half of the body and gray in the upper half of the body. The yellow eyes are characteristic of the ide. On average, the pieces caught are between 30 and 50 cm long. He is often confused with roach, chub or gag.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'https://angloo.com/wp-content/uploads/jaź-300x143.jpg',
                                                                                                                                                                                                ' Lakes, canals, rivers, in particular their middle course. We can often meet him near the shore near trees, from where food falls on the surface of the water. In colder seasons, e.g. in autumn, it swims deeper, in warmer seasons closer to the surface. Bottom depressions are also his seat. It is important to note that the polluted waters are not of interest to the weir, so it can be found in clean estuaries and slightly turbid waters.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Ide is active throughout the year. May, August and September are the best months for jazz, because then it is active almost all day.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Peas, white worms, pins, live insects. Small animal and vegetable baits.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Any loose chub and chub blends. In addition, peas, corn and other grains.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'The main method is a float, or more specifically, a fishbowl (early autumn), in a warmer ground - a feeder. Many people go fishing with spinning. Appropriate behavior in the fishery is important. First of all, you need to keep quiet along with the silent casting of the rod. The color of clothing is also important, as it may not be grossly different from the color of the surroundings.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Ides is caught with different techniques. Spinning: Lovers of this method should remember about more delicate equipment - rod up to 240 - 270 cm with casting weight up to 15-20 grams, fishing line 0.18 mm. Ground: Preferably feeder 360 - 390 cm, casting weight up to 80-100 grams. Main line max. 0.20 or 0.22 mm. Hook number 10-14. Float: Rod up to 5 meters long, float up to 4-5 grams.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'rivers from the Vistula to the Oder, Bug, Warta and others, standing waters, lakes, canals, dam reservoirs',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'no protection period',
                                                                                                                                                                                                '25 cm',
                                                                                                                                                                                                '78 and 82 cm and 5.10 kg');
