                                                                                                                                                                                                'DACE (Leuciscus leuciscus)',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'carp family',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'In Poland, this fish is less often caught. It occurs in rivers with a sandy base and strong current, streams and lakes. It can also be found in the Baltic Sea in bays with low salinity.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'https://angloo.com/wp-content/uploads/jelec-300x139.jpg',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'It reaches a length of about 35 cm and a weight of 250g. The body is slender and strongly flattened laterally. Coloration from black-blue with a metallic gloss on the back to white-yellow on the belly with a weak gloss. Fins generally pale yellowish or slightly orange. Dorsal and caudal fins are usually more intensely colored.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Warmer seasons. From spring to autumn.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'White worms, pins, red worms. Small fly lures.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Any mixes of roach and other carp species, as well as universal groundbait.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Mainly float, occasionally ground and fly fishing methods.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'Float - should have a small maximum two-gram float, thin 0.16-0.18 mm.',
                                                                                                                                                                                                'mainly rivers, oxbow lakes, canals',
